This paper discusses model-based reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning and artificial intelligence. The use of Lipschitz continuity and the Wasserstein metric suggests a focus on optimization and mathematical analysis, which are common in the subfields of machine learning and optimization. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also discusses the challenges of learning a useful model in the approximate setting, which suggests a focus on data science and statistics, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.ML (Machine Learning) also likely sub-categories.
